SIMPLE: falsehood
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Falsehood
<hw>False"hood</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>False</ets> +
<ets>-hood</ets>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Want of truth or accuracy; an
untrue assertion or representation; error; misrepresentation;
falsity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though it be a lie in the clock, it is but a <qex>falsehood</qex>
in the hand of the dial when pointing at a wrong hour, if rightly
following the direction of the wheel which moveth it.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A deliberate intentional assertion of what is known
to be untrue; a departure from moral integrity; a lie.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Treachery; deceit; perfidy;
unfaithfulness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Betrayed by <qex>falsehood</qex> of his guard.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A counterfeit; a false appearance; an
imposture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For his molten image is <qex>falsehood</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. x.
14.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No <qex>falsehood</qex> can endure⟦br⟧
Touch of celestial temper.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Falsity; lie; untruth; fiction; fabrication. See
<er>Falsity</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Falsely</ent>⟦br⟧
